Sentencas: Ceramic anodes have many advantages over cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We report the synthesis and characterization of Sn doped double perovskite PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta (x = 0-0.3) anode materials.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Different crystal structures were observed depending on the Sn doping level and gas atmosphere.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The materials demonstrated excellent stability in both reducing and redox atmospheres at elevated temperatures.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen content in the as-prepared PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta was nonlinearly correlated to the Sn doping level and reached maximum values around x = 0.1.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After the reducing treatment, the oxygen content linearly decreased with increasing Sn doping level.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of bulk PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta (x = 0.1) reached 63.6 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C in humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the surface exchange coefficient and bulk diffusivity of PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta reached the maximum values of 4.42 x 10(-6) ms(-1) and 6.04 x 10(-7) m(2) s(-1), respectively, in the reducing process when the Sn doping level was x = 0.1.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activation energies of surface exchange coefficient and bulk diffusivity of PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta (x = 0.1) were 0.22 eV and 0.16 eV, respectively, in the reducing process.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance of the PrBaFe(2-x) SnxO5+delta (x = 0.1) anode was 0.095-0.285 Omega cm(2) from 850-750 degrees C in humidified hydrogen, better than or comparable to the best ceramic anodes in the literature.
Titulo: Tin doped PrBaFe2O5+δ anode material for solid oxide fuel cells
